      <section name='coin'>

         <para number='1' comment='Get coin - option 1'>
         You thrust your hand (or equivalent) into the cold water and rummage through the rubbish, finally seizing on a shiny little coin. It looks like it might be an ancient silver Imperial Groat! Trembling with excitement, you try to get a grip on the coin but it is stuck firmly to the floor of the conduit. You take your hand out of the cold water and thrust it into your pocket to warm up before you try again.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Get coin - option 2'>
         You thrust your hand (or equivalent) into the cold water and rummage through the rubbish until you feel your fingers sinking into something squishy. You shudder at the disgusting sensation and a wave of weakness washes over you. You jerk your hand out, shaking it and rubbing it against your clothes to wipe away the slime before you try again.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='key'>

         <para number='1' comment='Get key - option 1'>
         You thrust your hand (or equivalent) into the cold water and rummage through the rubbish, finally seizing on an old key. It shines softly in the dim light of the sewer. You tuck the key safely into your pocket wondering what lock it might open.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Get key - option 2'>
         You thrust your hand (or equivalent) into the cold water and rummage through the rubbish until you feel your fingers sinking into something squishy. You shudder at the disgusting sensation and a wave of weakness washes over you.  You jerk your hand out, shaking it and rubbing it against your clothes to wipe away the slime before you try again.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Get key - option 3'>
         You thrust your hand (or equivalent) into the cold water and rummage through the rubbish, finally seizing on an old key. The key is rusty and the end is broken off; it's obviously useless and you throw it back into the water before trying again.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='Drop key'>
         The key hits the ground and before you can react, the Oldman comes along and says, "I've been looking for that." He bends over and grabs the key and is gone.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='329 - put key in lock - got key'>
         The key passes effortlessly through the force field and slides gently into the lock. You hear a faint click and whirring buzz as ancient circuits activate and when you turn the doorknob, the door swings open. The key seems to have fused to the lock so you abandon it and step into the dark room beyond.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='No key'>
         You search your pockets but can't find any keys to fit an ancient metal lock.
         </para>

